South Africa’s restaurants are gearing up to reopen amid the coronavirus pandemic. Many won't be able to employ all their staff and some aren't to reopening their doors. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Restaurant Association of South Africa is appealing with government to urgently publish trading regulations. The association's CEO Wendy Alberts says they have been ready to reopen for weeks and the delays are further crippling the industry. "I don't know why they don't understand the urgency of how crippled our industry is and how completely decimated the restaurant industry is. READ: Sit-down restaurants on the brink "It is imperative, we have put all the proposed measures in place to advocate through government, Cogta on our responsibility, and our readiness to open. We are absolutely ready to open today," she said. Alberts says they are ready to get back to business. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.